@page "/docs/extensions/reporting/designer"

<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/reporting/designer" Title="Blazorise Reporting designer" Description="Configure the Blazorise Reporting designer, toolbar, viewer, and report state." />

<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/Reporting/Designer" AddedVersion="New">
    Reporting designer
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Enable design mode when users should edit the report template, move elements, edit properties, and switch between design and preview.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Designer and toolbar">
        The toolbar is declarative and can be grouped. Built-in commands cover designer panes, editing, history, data-source connection, PDF download, and mode switching.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent Code="ReportingDesignerToolbarExample" Outlined FullWidth>
        <ReportingDesignerToolbarExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
</DocsPageSection>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    The default designer toolbar includes a panes menu. When defining a custom toolbar, add <Code Tag>ReportToolbarPanesMenu</Code> if users should be able to open, focus, or show flyout panes from the toolbar.
    Designer panes can also be pinned or unpinned from their headers.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="State">
        Bind the report definition when the designer output should be saved, restored, or sent to a server.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent Code="ReportingStateExample" Outlined FullWidth>
        <ReportingStateExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
</DocsPageSection>